<item>
            <title>[ENTESB-5806] allow leveldb to be used as an aggregation store for consumers in an &quot;exclusive consumer&quot; configuration</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-5806</link>
                <project id="12314570" key="ENTESB">JBoss Fuse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When consumers that utilize an aggregation store are set up for failover (exclusive consumer configuration), a leveldb repository is desired as an alternative to a JDBC store.  Currently, when the second consumer attempts to connect to the leveldb store, it cannot obtain the lock on the database and the camel route fails/shuts down.  Desired behavior is for the second consumer to connect to the aggregation repository, wait to become the exclusive consumer, and then start processing aggregations.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
